OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FJail people for Post Office
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fscandal, says minister     
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The Post Office minister has told the  
OL,6, BBC that those responsible for the     
OL,7, Horizon scandal "should go to jail"    
OL,9,FKevin Hollinrake told a BBC Breakfast  
OL,10,Faudience of sub-postmasters that       
OL,11,F"people should be prosecuted" when     
OL,12,Fevidence is "established", and "people 
OL,13,Fwithin the Post Office, possibly       
OL,14,Ffurther afield, should go to jail".    
OL,16,FMore than 700 people were prosecuted by
OL,17,Fthe Post Office between 1999 and 2015. 
OL,19,FTo date, just 37 have received full and
OL,20,Ffinal compensation settlements.        
